monogr.title: Ad Hugonem Eterialium doctorem suum et utraque origine fratrem Leo Tuscus imperatoriarum epistolarum interpres de sompniis et oraculis.
De sompniis et oraculis

projectDesc.p: This digital corpus is part of the thesis project "Oneirocriticon Latinum" being realized by Pierre-Olivier Beaulnes under the direction of Prof. Cédric Giraud.

correction.p: The segmentation was corrected manually and the transcription from the OCR was corrected.

normalization.p: For regularisation purposes, this transcription has in part been standardised using a Python script.

zone.line: Q
Ad Hugonẽ eterialiũ doctorẽ suũ & utͣq origine fr̃em
leo tuscꝰ imꝑatoriarũ. epłarũ int̃pres de sõpniis ⁊ oracłis.
Uamqͣm optime preceptor inuictũ imperatorẽ
manuel ꝑ fines sequar bitinie licaonieq fugantẽ
ꝑsas flexipedũ hederarũ ꝯplectentes uestigia. tñ
memorandi nõ sũ oblitꝰ sompnii a te uisi qͥ dictũ
inexpugnabilẽ uirũ eneo in eqͦ suꝑͣ colũpnã qͣm traces dicunt
augustiana bizancii sito nobilit̃ sedere ꝯspicabaris eodẽ autẽ
in loco doctissimis qͥbꝰdam astantibꝰ latinis romana orõne cũ in
qͦdam legeret libello interpellanti tͥ soli fauorẽ p̃stitisse uisus ẽ
latuit tũc utrũq nr̃m ea quid portende̾t uisio at uͦ eiusmodi
oracłm editꝰ ꝑ te de filii hoĩs minoritate ad peͣtrẽ deũ libellus tp̃e
post reuelauit sub tegumentis Profecto eneus ille sonipes
aĩa carens altissime sonantissimeq q̃onis erat qͤ int̃ grecos
uersabat᷑ uentilatio u̾bũ ẜ dei scđm qđ incarnatũ patͥ eqͣle
ꝓtestans ratõnis ueritatisq radicitꝰ expers ut qͣdrupes noĩatꝰ
Soluit autẽ illã controu̾siã clamitante dicto libello augustał
clemencie decretũ pauco scandali fomento ꝯtͣ uoluntatẽ illius
relicto Ex eo gͥ tp̃e pectus sollicitudine ꝑcussi sub corde ignitos
u̾saui carbones cogitando uti lene eẽt annõ si onirocriti g̾coꝵ
pħis ariolanti loqͥ latine ꝑsuaderẽ enucleatim atq inoffensã
ꝑspicuitatẽ figmenti sõpnialis tuo fauore nr̃oꝵ tuscoꝵ desiđio
breuit̃ reserarem Qͦs qͥdẽ fluctu ꝑcupio asꝑgi undiosiore ut irri-
gent᷑ affatĩ efficiant᷑q fecundiores Nam seres ut fert᷑ arbores suas
undis asꝑgunt qnͣ uberiorẽ lanuginẽ que sericũ admitt̃e nĩ-
tunt᷑ Ceterũ haut facile ẽ in huiꝰmodi uersari pelago cuiꝰ lati-
tudo ad aures usq dehiscit nõ sponte remigẽ asciscens inualidũ
Non solũ enĩ subtilibꝰ expositũ inuestigatõnib & illos repellũt
qui debilitate pedũ serpunt ut antipodes & eos qui nõ mouent
linguas ut ꝑleraq aquatiliũ set neq monoxilo se nauigari li-
mine patit᷑ Qͣm ob rem loquelã imꝑatorioꝵ int̃pretatõnibus
apicũ obseqͤntẽ ꝑ excubias int̃dũ huic tnͣslatõni nõ irrita
spe addixi totũ opꝰ sapiencie tue dicaturus iudicio mei qͥdem
auctoris tui uͦ ꝓbatoris equilibre pensans incertũ Nã tuum
examen discernere nõ sũ ambiguus qͥcqͥd arida exsanguisq
poscit ratiocinatõ Set enĩ desiderantissimꝰ nepos fabriciꝰ gͤcarũ
sciolus & ip̃e litterarũ sõpnaliũ figmentoꝵ odoratus rosaria
scribendi assiduitate me a confluentibꝰ eleuat prestatq nõ me-
diocre adiumentũ Atq iccirco neq nomen sine subiecto neq
sine uiribꝰ erit edicio sidoneis tirenisq sagittis parũ penetͣ-
bilis apparitura ut arbitror Ergo qͥsqͥs nodosoꝵ sõpnioꝵ fa-
tigat᷑ inuolucris si ꝑ aliqͦd hic scriptoꝵ absolui postulet caue-
at pretẽptare plus nosse qͣm sat est ne titulos deprauet apolli-
nee urbis ambiguũ rimis herbidisq sentibꝰ Ego autẽ tui soliꝰ
utrarũq linguarũ peritissimo examini uolumen hoc subpo-
no ut in eo que arescunt ac caligant per te illustrata orbi de-
mũ succincta ꝓfessione uulgent᷑.
